// D1 cartridge registry — shared between the LabelManager and
// LabelWriter (Duo tape side) drivers.
//
// Both repos consume this catalogue from `@thermal-label/d1-core` so
// the SKUs, colour metadata, and per-width raster constants stay in
// lockstep across the family. Driver-specific catalogues (LW paper
// rolls, LM device-specific defaults) live in their own repos.
//
// ─── Width tiers ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
// D1 chassis come in three mechanical tiers. Each accepts every
// smaller cassette as well; pickers should match on the appropriate
// `targetModels` key:
//
//   tier      sizes (mm)        targetModels    mediaCompatibility
//   ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
//   12 mm     6 / 9 / 12        ['d1']          ['d1']
//   19 mm     + 19              ['d1-wide']     ['d1', 'd1-wide']
//   24 mm     + 24              ['d1-24']       ['d1', 'd1-wide', 'd1-24']
//
// Note: the LabelManager driver's encoder caps the printable raster
// at 64 dots (head pitch on every catalogued LM chassis), so 19mm
// cartridges print on a centred ~9mm strip. 24mm support requires the
// 128-dot Duo tape head; the encoder narrows raster width to
// `min(media.printableDots, engine.headDots)` either way.
//
// ─── Catalogue fields ────────────────────────────────────────────
//   - `material`        D1 substrate family (standard / permanent-
//                       polyester / flexible-nylon / durable /
//                       rhino-*). Picker UX hint.
//   - `text`            Printed colour, named (the only ink the
//                       cartridge carries).
//   - `background`      Substrate colour, named.
//   - `tapeWidthMm`     Physical cassette width (6/9/12/19/24).
//   - `printableDots`   Per-cartridge raster width — what the encoder
//                       sets `ESC D N` from. 6→32, 9→48, 12→64,
//                       19→64 (capped at 12mm head), 24→128.
//   - `bytesPerLine`    `ceil(printableDots / 8)`.
//
// ─── Rhino™ industrial cartridges (rhino-*) ──────────────────────
// DYMO's Rhino industrial line uses cartridges that are mechanically
// the same shape as D1 and physically fit LabelManager chassis and
// the LabelWriter Duo tape side; community reports
// (silvenga.com/posts/tip-dymo-label-compatibility,
// dymo-label-printers.co.uk FAQ) corroborate the cross-fit. DYMO
// does not officially endorse the cross-use, and the stiffer
// industrial substrates — heat-shrink polyolefin and durable
// polyester especially — accelerate cutter blade and motor wear over
// time. Project assumes no responsibility for wear, damage, or
// warranty implications.
//
// SKUs transcribed from the official DYMO Industrial Labels
// datasheet. 24mm Rhino entries (and the Rhino self-laminating line,
// which is 24mm-only) are not yet catalogued — add as authoritative
// SKU sources surface.
[
  // ─── 6 mm — Standard ─────────────────────────────────────────────
  {
    id: 'd1-standard-bw-6',
